article.headline: Indiana St. 76, N. Iowa 74
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa -- Jake Odum and Jordan Printy each scored 17 points and Indiana State held off Northern Iowa 76-74 Tuesday night to clinch the No. 3 seed for next week's Missouri Valley tournament. RJ Mahurin added 11 points, and the Sycamores (16-13, 11-6) guaranteed themselves a winning record in consecutive regular seasons for the first time since 1999-2000 and 2000-01. Anthony James scored 18 points and Johnny Moran had 17 for the Panthers (19-11, 10-7), who have lost four of five following a season-high eight-game losing streak. Leading 50-49 with 7:38 to play, Indiana State went on a 10-2 run to match its biggest lead, 60-51 with 4:43 remaining. Northern Iowa then rallied within 75-74 on Kwadzo Ahelegbe's 3-pointer with 5 seconds to go, but the Panthers failed to attempt another shot.
